<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE0FFD4FDFAF979FD92F911" box="[514,585,1689,1715]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,594,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[159,1427,589,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 5. Adults of Pterotopteryx. 2 – 3, P. nigrifasciata sp. nov.; 4 – 5, P. vietana sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175222/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FDC2F979FD92F911" box="[570,585,1689,1715]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) densely scaled, pale yellowish brown. Labial palpus blackish gray dorsally, about 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FEDCF921FEE9F979" box="[292,306,1729,1755]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
times as long as horizontal diameter of compound eye; 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FC3DF921FC08F979" box="[965,979,1729,1755]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
nd segment with fuscous band near the base, 1.2 times as long as horizontal diameter of compound eye; 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FC5BF909FC6BF8A1" box="[931,944,1769,1795]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="3.0">3</number>
rd segment creamy white, slender, with a fuscous band preapically, pointed apically, as long as 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FCE9F8F4FCC4F88C" box="[785,799,1812,1838]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
nd segment. Thorax (
<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE0FFD4FBF6F8F4FB8FF88C" box="[1038,1108,1812,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,270,1464,1488]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,594,1433]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[159,1427,589,1441]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 5. Adults of Pterotopteryx. 2 – 3, P. nigrifasciata sp. nov.; 4 – 5, P. vietana sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175222/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FBBDF8F4FB8FF88C" box="[1093,1108,1812,1838]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) pale brownish yellow dorsally, triangular in outline. Abdomen with creamy white line on each segment dorsally. Wingspan 
<quantity id="4CCB9B52FFE0FFD4FAE1F8DCFA40F8F4" box="[1305,1435,1852,1878]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15 mm</quantity>
. Forewing pale grayish brown, divided into six lobes, deeply emarginated at the first cleft; 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FB4DF887FB18F823" box="[1205,1219,1895,1921]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
st lobe rather thick, ground color pale yellowish brown, with four large blackish brown spots, all spots with whitish marginal line laterally; spot I near the point of branching between 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FD0FF85AFCDEF876" box="[759,773,1978,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
st and 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE0FFD4FCBFF85AFC8DF876" box="[839,854,1978,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="2.0">2</number>
nd lobes; spots II and III on middle at regular interval; spot IV before apex; median fascia on 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FD73FF7AFD41FF16" box="[651,666,154,180]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
nd– 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FD42FF7AFD1CFF16" box="[698,711,154,180]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
th lobes located at level of 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FC00FF7AFBDDFF16" box="[1016,1030,154,180]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
nd spot of 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FB8CFF7AFB58FF16" box="[1140,1155,154,180]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
st lobe, with spot of similar width as II of 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FE89FF25FEA4FF7D" box="[369,383,197,223]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
st lobe; subterminal spots on 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FD2BFF25FD39FF7D" box="[723,738,197,223]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
nd– 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FCFAFF25FCCBFF7D" box="[770,784,197,223]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
th lobes between costal spot III and IV. Hindwing lobes similar to those of forewing, but somewhat slender and weaker.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36B7FFE1FFD5FF3FFEF5FAB5FD87" blockId="3.[151,1438,152,869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B947EAA5FFE1FFD5FF3FFEF5FEA3FE8D" bold="true" box="[199,376,277,303]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE1FFD5FE72FEF5FE08FE8D" box="[394,467,277,303]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[197,1337,928,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,908,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 7. Male genitalia and abdomen of Pterotopteryx nigrifasciata sp. nov. 6, male genitalia; 7, abdomen (scale bars: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175223/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FE3CFEF5FE08FE8D" box="[452,467,277,303]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
a–c). Tegumen narrow, well sclerotized near base of uncus. Uncus narrow, fairly long, uniform in width, rather thick with somewhat round apex. Gnathos long, thick, nearly as long as uncus, slightly narrowed terminally. Valva somewhat broadened in distal half, membranous, rounded terminally. Juxta long, sickle­shaped, membranous, slightly broadened beyond middle. Phallus (
<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE1FFD5FB7EFE6DFB15FE05" box="[1158,1230,397,423]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[197,1337,928,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,908,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 7. Male genitalia and abdomen of Pterotopteryx nigrifasciata sp. nov. 6, male genitalia; 7, abdomen (scale bars: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175223/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FB47FE6DFB15FE05" box="[1215,1230,397,423]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
c) nearly straight, heavily sclerotized ventrally, longer than valva; coecum as long as valva; a large horn­shaped cornutus in vesica. Vinculum short, cone­shaped, within folded 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FD36FE01FD07FE59" box="[718,732,481,507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="8.0">8</number>
th abdominal segment (
<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE1FFD5FC1CFE01FBF1FE59" box="[996,1066,481,507]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[197,1337,928,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,908,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 7. Male genitalia and abdomen of Pterotopteryx nigrifasciata sp. nov. 6, male genitalia; 7, abdomen (scale bars: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175223/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FBE2FE01FBF1FE59" box="[1050,1066,481,507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
b); 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FBA9FE01FB84FE59" box="[1105,1119,481,507]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="8.0">8</number>
th sternite seed­shaped, narrowed terminally. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE1FFD5FE08FDEBFDEDFD87" box="[496,566,523,549]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 7" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[197,1337,928,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[153,1433,908,1782]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 7. Male genitalia and abdomen of Pterotopteryx nigrifasciata sp. nov. 6, male genitalia; 7, abdomen (scale bars: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175223/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FDDFFDEBFDEDFD87" box="[551,566,523,549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
) with an upper liplike sclerotized part on each segment from 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FAF0FDEBFACDFD87" box="[1288,1302,523,549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
nd to 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FAB4FDEBFA81FD87" box="[1356,1370,523,549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="6.0">6</number>
th.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8C36B7FFE1FFD5FF3FFDD3FBFDFD4F" blockId="3.[151,1438,152,869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B947EAA5FFE1FFD5FF3FFDD3FE48FDEF" bold="true" box="[199,403,563,589]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE1FFD5FE5CFDD3FE37FDEF" box="[420,492,563,589]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 – 9" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1752,1776]" captionTargetBox="[209,1265,666,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[156,1431,653,1745]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8 – 9. Female genitalia of Pterotopteryx. 8, P. nigrifasciata sp. nov.; 9, P. vietana sp. nov. (scale bars: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175224/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FE24FDD3FE37FDEF" box="[476,492,563,589]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Papilla analis slightly rolled inward near middle. Apophysis anterioris as long as posterioris. Ostium bursae wine glass­shaped; postvaginal plate oblong. Corpus bursae short, ovate, membranous, minutely granulated on entire surface; signum absent. Ductus bursae nearly as long as corpus bursae, slightly widened beyond 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FE35FD4BFE03FD67" box="[461,472,683,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FE1BFD4BFE29FD67" box="[483,498,683,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
towards corpus bursae; ductus seminalis arising from 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FB6FFD4BFB7DFD67" box="[1175,1190,683,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FB57FD4BFB67FD67" box="[1199,1212,683,709]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="3.0">3</number>
of ductus bursae. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13082A32FFE1FFD5FEE2FD33FEB4FD4F" box="[282,367,723,749]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 11" captionStartId="5.[151,270,1662,1686]" captionTargetBox="[223,1317,725,1624]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[153,1433,704,1654]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 11. Female abdomen of Pterotopteryx. 10, P. nigrifasciata sp. nov.; 10, P. vietana sp. nov. (scale bars: 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/175225/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
Fig. 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FEA9FD33FEB4FD4F" box="[337,367,723,749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) with upper liplike sclerotized part on each segment 
<number id="3DFB2490FFE1FFD5FC23FD33FBFAFD4F" box="[987,1057,723,749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2 to 6</number>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329653CFFE1FFD5FF3FFD1BFDE9FCB7" box="[199,562,763,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8C36B7FFE1FFD5FF3FFD1BFDE9FCB7" blockId="3.[151,1438,152,869]" box="[199,562,763,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B947EAA5FFE1FFD5FF3FFD1BFE82FCB7" bold="true" box="[199,345,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F3247627FFE1FFD5FE90FD1BFE10FCB7" box="[360,459,763,789]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(North).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C329653CFFE1FFD5FF3FFCC3FD05FCC7" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8C36B7FFE1FFD5FF3FFCC3FD05FCC7" blockId="3.[151,1438,152,869]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B947EAA5FFE1FFD5FF3FFCC3FE9DFC9F" bold="true" box="[199,326,803,829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin niger (= black) and fascia (= band), referring to the characteristic wing pattern of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
